WEBVTT

1
00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:59.000
<c.transcription>［ワキツレ］そもそもこれは</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] To begin with,)</c>

2
00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:04.000
<c.transcription>一條の院に仕へ奉る。</c>
<c.translation>(I am in the service of the Emperor Ichijo.)</c>

3
00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:12.000
<c.transcription>橘の道成とは我が事なり。</c>
<c.translation>(I am known as Tachibana no Michinari.)</c>

4
00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:22.000
<c.transcription>さても帝今夜奇特の御霊夢ましまして。</c>
<c.translation>(It so happens that his Lordship)</c>

5
00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:28.000
<c.transcription>三条の小鍛冶宗近に。</c>
<c.translation>(has this night had a portentous dream oracle.)</c>

6
00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:34.000
<c.transcription>御剣を打たせらるべきとの</c>
<c.translation>(The Sanjo swordsmith Munechika)</c>

7
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:43.000
<c.transcription>宣旨只今成り下りて候程に。</c>
<c.translation>(must be ordered to forge a blade.)</c>

8
00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:50.000
<c.transcription>この由を宗近に申し付ばやと</c>
<c.translation>(I am on my way now to tell Munechika)</c>

9
00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:54.000
<c.transcription>存候う。</c>
<c.translation>(of this matter.)</c>

10
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:25.000
<c.transcription>［ワキツレ］いかに此の内に宗近のわたり候か。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] Is Munechika at home ?)</c>

11
00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:38.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］誰にてわたり候ふぞ。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Who is it that has come here ?)</c>

12
00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:47.000
<c.transcription>［ワキツレ］是は宣旨にて候。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] I am a messenger from the Emperor.)</c>

13
00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:55.000
<c.transcription>我が君今夜不思議の霊夢ましまして。</c>
<c.translation>(His Majesty has this night had a marvelous oracle in a dream.)</c>

14
00:05:55.000 --> 00:06:05.000
<c.transcription>御剣を打たせられるべしとの御事なり。</c>
<c.translation>(According to the oracle, you must forge a fine sword for him.)</c>

15
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:11.000
<c.transcription>とうとう仕り候へ。</c>
<c.translation>(Please comply with this order at once.)</c>

16
00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:24.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］宣旨畏つて承り候 さりながら</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] While I certainly must agree to execute this imperial order,)</c>

17
00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:33.000
<c.transcription>折節相鎚打つべきものの無く候をば</c>
<c.translation>(as I do not have anyone to assist me,)</c>

18
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:40.000
<c.transcription>何とつかまつり候べき。</c>
<c.translation>(I do not know how I will be able to carry it out.)</c>

19
00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:46.000
<c.transcription>［ワキツレ］不思議の事を申すものかな。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] What you say sir, seems most strange.)</c>

20
00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:53.000
<c.transcription>その名を得たる何時なるが</c>
<c.translation>(To hear that someone of your reputation)</c>

21
00:06:53.000 --> 00:07:00.000
<c.transcription>相鎚打つべきものの無きとは。</c>
<c.translation>(does not have an appropriate assistant,)</c>

22
00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:06.000
<c.transcription>心得難き言い事かな。</c>
<c.translation>(is the most unfortunate news.)</c>

23
00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:14.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］これは仰せにて候へども</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Even though I am commanded to do so,)</c>

24
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:23.000
<c.transcription>かようの一大事の物を仕るには</c>
<c.translation>(without an assistant whose skills are equal to my own,)</c>

25
00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:34.000
<c.transcription>我に劣らぬ程の物の相鎚仕りてこそ。</c>
<c.translation>(it will not be possible to fulfill this order)</c>

26
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:42.000
<c.transcription>御剣をも打ち申すべけれ</c>
<c.translation>(to forge an imperial blade.)</c>

27
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:50.000
<c.transcription>とにかくに御返事を申しかね。</c>
<c.translation>(This is the answer I must give,)</c>

28
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:56.000
<c.transcription>赤面さしたるばかりなり。</c>
<c.translation>(though I am overcome with embarassment.)</c>

29
00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:03.000
<c.transcription>［ワキツレ］申すところはさることなれども。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] Even though it may be as you say,)</c>

30
00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:11.000
<c.transcription>帝も不思議の霊夢ましませば。</c>
<c.translation>(yet as this is the Emperor's wonderful dream oracle,)</c>

31
00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:17.000
<c.transcription>いかなることか候べき</c>
<c.translation>(it surely must be relied upon)</c>

32
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:25.000
<c.transcription>頼もしく思ひ申しつつ</c>
<c.translation>(and you must quickly say)</c>

33
00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:33.000
<c.transcription>はやはや領掌申すべしと</c>
<c.translation>(you will accept the order.)</c>

34
00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:42.000
<c.transcription>重ねて宣旨ありければ。</c>
<c.translation>(Let me repeat the imperial command!)</c>

35
00:08:42.000 --> 00:09:10.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］此上はとにもかくにも宗近が</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] At this point, in any case, Munechika)</c>

36
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:27.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］とにもかくにも宗近が</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] In any case, Munechika)</c>

37
00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:38.000
<c.transcription>進退ここに谷まりて</c>
<c.translation>(must here decide his course of action.)</c>

38
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:55.000
<c.transcription>御剣の刃の乱るゝ心なりけり。</c>
<c.translation>(Like the ripples beaten along a well-forged blade, his heart wavers.)</c>

39
00:09:55.000 --> 00:10:11.000
<c.transcription>さりながら御政道 直なる今の御代なれば。</c>
<c.translation>(Yet, as the reign in the present age is righteous,)</c>

40
00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:20.000
<c.transcription>若しも奇特のありやせん。</c>
<c.translation>(a miracle may well be afforded me.)</c>

41
00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:30.000
<c.transcription>それのみ頼む心かな。</c>
<c.translation>(I must place my trust only in this.)</c>

42
00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:45.000
<c.transcription>それのみ頼む心かな。</c>
<c.translation>(I must place my trust only in this.)</c>

43
00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:55.000
<c.transcription>［ワキツレ］宣旨に任せとうとう御剣を仕り候へ。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKIZURE] Hurry and make the sword.)</c>

44
00:10:55.000 --> 00:11:00.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］畏って候。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Yes, sir.)</c>

45
00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:32.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］これは一大事を仰せ出されて候ふものかな。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] This is a great task you have come to give me.)</c>

46
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:44.000
<c.transcription>かやうの御事は神力を頼むならは別義なく候。</c>
<c.translation>(Such a command can be carried out if I ask for divine help.)</c>

47
00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:56.000
<c.transcription>某が氏の神は稲荷の明神にて候程に。</c>
<c.translation>(As my family deity is Inari no Myojin,)</c>

48
00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:04.000
<c.transcription>これより直に稲荷に参り。</c>
<c.translation>(I will go at once to Inari,)</c>

49
00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:15.000
<c.transcription>この事祈誓申さばやと存じ候。</c>
<c.translation>(and pray concerning this matter.)</c>

50
00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:52.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］なう／＼あれなるは三条の小鍛冶宗近にて御入り候ふか。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] Ho there! Is that the Swordsmith of Sanjō, Munechika ?)</c>

51
00:12:52.000 --> 00:13:02.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］不思議やななべてならざる御事の。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] How mysterious! Here is someone who is certainly not an ordinary person.)</c>

52
00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:10.000
<c.transcription>道もなき方より来たり給ひ</c>
<c.translation>(There is no path from the direction from which he has appeared,)</c>

53
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:16.000
<c.transcription>我が名をさして宣ふは。</c>
<c.translation>(and now he has called me by name.)</c>

54
00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:24.000
<c.transcription>いかなる人にてましますぞ。</c>
<c.translation>(What manner of man are you ?)</c>

55
00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:34.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］雲の上なる君よりも</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] You have been ordered)</c>

56
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:44.000
<c.transcription>剣を打ちて参らせよと。</c>
<c.translation>(by his Imperial Majesty)</c>

57
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:53.000
<c.transcription>汝に仰せありしよなう。</c>
<c.translation>(to forge a sword!)</c>

58
00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:58.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］さればこそ</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] As I thought, you are not what you seem to be,)</c>

59
00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:08.000
<c.transcription>それにつけてもなほ／＼奇特の御事なれ。</c>
<c.translation>(and events must be of great importance indeed.)</c>

60
00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:14.000
<c.transcription>剣の勅も只今なるを。</c>
<c.translation>(I have just received the order to make a blade!)</c>

61
00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:21.000
<c.transcription>早くも知ろしめさるる事</c>
<c.translation>(How could it be that anyone could know so soon ?)</c>

62
00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:28.000
<c.transcription>返す／＼も不審なり。</c>
<c.translation>(No matter how I consider it, the matter is most strange.)</c>

63
00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:38.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］げにげにそれはさる事なれども</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] In truth, it is as you say. It is said: To know a thing one's self,)</c>

64
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:46.000
<c.transcription>我のみ知れば諸人までも。</c>
<c.translation>(is to find it known to all.)</c>

65
00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:52.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］天に声あり。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] A voice in heaven,)</c>

66
00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:58.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］地に響く。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] echoes on the earth!)</c>

67
00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:03.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］壁に耳。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Wall have ears:)</c>

68
00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:19.000
<c.transcription>岩の物いふ世の中に</c>
<c.translation>(In the world where rocks may speak,)</c>

69
00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:37.000
<c.transcription>岩の物いふ世の中に。</c>
<c.translation>(In the world where rocks may speak,)</c>

70
00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:52.000
<c.transcription>隠はあらじ殊になほ。</c>
<c.translation>(and nothing is hidden,)</c>

71
00:15:52.000 --> 00:16:03.000
<c.transcription>雲の上人の御剣の。</c>
<c.translation>(nothing shall dim the radiance)</c>

72
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:14.000
<c.transcription>光は何か闇からん。</c>
<c.translation>(of the Emperor's sword.)</c>

73
00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:21.000
<c.transcription>唯頼めこの君の。</c>
<c.translation>(Only have faith)</c>

74
00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:31.000
<c.transcription>恵によらば御剣も</c>
<c.translation>(that through his Majesty's grace and the sword)</c>

75
00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:40.000
<c.transcription>などか心に適はざる。</c>
<c.translation>(will be realized as you wish.)</c>

76
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:55.000
<c.transcription>などかは適はざるべき。</c>
<c.translation>(It must be realized.)</c>

77
00:16:55.000 --> 00:17:09.000
<c.transcription>それ漢王三尺の剣</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Once with such a blade, the Emperor's Three Foot Sword,)</c>

78
00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:18.000
<c.transcription>居ながら秦の乱を治め。</c>
<c.translation>(subdued the rebellion of the Ts'in by its reputation alone.)</c>

79
00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:25.000
<c.transcription>又煬帝がけいの剣。</c>
<c.translation>(Again, the Yang Emperor, with his sword Kei)</c>

80
00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:54.000
<c.transcription>周室の光を奪へり。</c>
<c.translation>(outshone the brillance of the House of Chou.)</c>

81
00:17:56.000 --> 00:18:11.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］その後玄宗皇帝の鍾馗大臣も</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] In later years, the Emperor Huan Tsung's Minister Chung K'ei too,)</c>

82
00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:18.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］剣の徳に魂魄は</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] joined his spirit after death with the virtue of his sword,)</c>

83
00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:24.000
<c.transcription>君辺に仕へ奉り。</c>
<c.translation>(and thus served at his Lord's side.)</c>

84
00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:33.000
<c.transcription>魍魎鬼神に至るまで。</c>
<c.translation>(Even evil spirits and demons)</c>

85
00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:40.000
<c.transcription>剣の刃の光。に恐れて</c>
<c.translation>(were in fear of that sword's glow,)</c>

86
00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:50.000
<c.transcription>其寇をなす事を得ず。</c>
<c.translation>(and the destruction they sought was not achieved.)</c>

87
00:18:50.000 --> 00:19:10.000
<c.transcription>漢家本朝に於て剣の威徳</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] Indeed, the virtue of the swords in China and Japan)</c>

88
00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:35.000
<c.transcription>申すに及ばぬ奇特とかや。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] and their miraculous power is beyond expression!)</c>

89
00:19:54.000 --> 00:20:09.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］また我が朝のそのはじめ。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] And so, it was in the early days of our history,)</c>

90
00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:27.000
<c.transcription>人皇十二代 景行天皇。</c>
<c.translation>(the Twelfth of the Imperial Line, the Emperor Keikō,)</c>

91
00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:38.000
<c.transcription>みこの尊の御名をば</c>
<c.translation>(had a son known by the name)</c>

92
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:51.000
<c.transcription>日本武と申しゝが。</c>
<c.translation>(Yamato-dake.)</c>

93
00:20:51.000 --> 00:21:10.000
<c.transcription>九夷を退治の勅を受け。</c>
<c.translation>(The wild barbarians! He received the order to subdue them.)</c>

94
00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:23.000
<c.transcription>関の東も遥なる。</c>
<c.translation>(The barrier check points far behind as yet further to the East.)</c>

95
00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:36.000
<c.transcription>東の旅の道すがら</c>
<c.translation>(The road of his journey to the Eastern provinces took him.)</c>

96
00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:54.000
<c.transcription>伊勢や尾張の海面に立つ波までも</c>
<c.translation>(Even at Ise and Owari the waves on the sea rise and return!)</c>

97
00:21:54.000 --> 00:22:02.000
<c.transcription>帰る事よと羨み。</c>
<c.translation>(With envy he wondered always,)</c>

98
00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:13.000
<c.transcription>いつかわれも帰る波の</c>
<c.translation>(when he too might find himself, with foam-drenched sleeves)</c>

99
00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:34.000
<c.transcription>衣手にあらめやと。思ひつゞけて行くほどに。</c>
<c.translation>(returning home, even as he continued on his way.)</c>

100
00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:52.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］こゝやかしこの戦に</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] In the battles in one place and in the next)</c>

101
00:22:52.000 --> 00:23:03.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］人馬巌窟に身を砕き</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] men and horses: their bodies crushed in their caverns,)</c>

102
00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:15.000
<c.transcription>血は涿鹿の川となって</c>
<c.translation>(their blood on the battlefields a river,)</c>

103
00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:28.000
<c.transcription>紅波盾流し数度に及べる夷も</c>
<c.translation>(their shields swept away on crimson waves again and again.)</c>

104
00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:35.000
<c.transcription>兜を脱いで矛を伏せ</c>
<c.translation>(Finally the barbarians removed their helmets,)</c>

105
00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:47.000
<c.transcription>皆降参を申しけり。</c>
<c.translation>(lay down their arms and were made to surrender.)</c>

106
00:23:47.000 --> 00:24:10.000
<c.transcription>尊の御宇より御狩場を始め給へり。</c>
<c.translation>(From the time of this Prince's reign, the royal sport of hunting was begun.)</c>

107
00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:30.000
<c.transcription>頃は神無月。</c>
<c.translation>(It was an incident that occurred,)</c>

108
00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:39.000
<c.transcription>二十日余りの事なれば。</c>
<c.translation>(on the twentieth day of the Tenth month:)</c>

109
00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:48.000
<c.transcription>四方の紅葉も冬枯の</c>
<c.translation>(Everywhere the autumn tints had faded,)</c>

110
00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:58.000
<c.transcription>遠山にかゝる薄雪を</c>
<c.translation>(and even on the distant winter withered mountains,)</c>

111
00:24:58.000 --> 00:25:10.000
<c.transcription>眺めさせ給ひしに。</c>
<c.translation>(the traces of the first snow fall could be seen.)</c>

112
00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:24.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］夷四方を囲みつゝ。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] The barbarians surrounding him on every side)</c>

113
00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:34.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］枯野の草に火をかけ</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Set fire to the grass of the withered fields, and as the blaze burned high)</c>

114
00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:44.000
<c.transcription>余炎しきりに燃え来たり</c>
<c.translation>(and as the blaze burned high with heavy lingering billows of smoke.)</c>

115
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:57.000
<c.transcription>かたき攻鼓を打ちかけて</c>
<c.translation>(Began to beat their war drums in the signal to attack.)</c>

116
00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:12.000
<c.transcription>火炎を放ちてかゝりければ。</c>
<c.translation>(The Towering flames! as the attack blazed forward)</c>

117
00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:22.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］尊は剣を抜いて。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] The Prince drew his sword)</c>

118
00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:28.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］尊は剣を抜いて。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] The Prince drawing his sword,)</c>

119
00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:37.000
<c.transcription>あたりを払ひ 忽ちに。</c>
<c.translation>(wielded it about him.)</c>

120
00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:44.000
<c.transcription>炎も立ち退けと</c>
<c.translation>(At once, the flames drew back,)</c>

121
00:26:44.000 --> 00:26:54.000
<c.transcription>四方の草を薙ぎ払へば。</c>
<c.translation>(as it mowed down the grasses in all directions.)</c>

122
00:26:54.000 --> 00:27:04.000
<c.transcription>剣の精霊嵐となつて</c>
<c.translation>(The spirit of the sword became a storm)</c>

123
00:27:04.000 --> 00:27:11.000
<c.transcription>炎も草も 吹き返されて。</c>
<c.translation>(blasting back the raging flames and grasses too.)</c>

124
00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:15.000
<c.transcription>天にかゞやき地に充ち／＼て。</c>
<c.translation>(The blaze lit up the heavens, covered the earth!)</c>

125
00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:22.000
<c.transcription>猛火は却つて敵を焼けば。</c>
<c.translation>(A furnace of fierce flames turned back to devour the enemy forces.)</c>

126
00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:27.000
<c.transcription>数万騎の夷どもは</c>
<c.translation>(Thus, the countless barbarians,)</c>

127
00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:36.000
<c.transcription>忽ちこゝにて失せてんげり。</c>
<c.translation>(and cavalrymen were brought down.)</c>

128
00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:48.000
<c.transcription>其後。四海治まりて</c>
<c.translation>(So in later years the Empire was at peace:)</c>

129
00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:56.000
<c.transcription>人家戸ざしを忘れしも。</c>
<c.translation>(So much so that the people forgot to bar the doors of their houses.)</c>

130
00:27:56.000 --> 00:28:05.000
<c.transcription>その草薙の故とかや。</c>
<c.translation>(This is because of the 'Grass-cutter', it was said.)</c>

131
00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:17.000
<c.transcription>只今汝が打つべき</c>
<c.translation>(And now, this auspicious omened blade)</c>

132
00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:23.000
<c.transcription>この瑞相の御剣も。</c>
<c.translation>(that you must forge!)</c>

133
00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:30.000
<c.transcription>いかでそれには劣るべき。</c>
<c.translation>(Is there any reason it should be a lesser blade than that ?)</c>

134
00:28:30.000 --> 00:28:43.000
<c.transcription>伝ふる家の宗近よ。</c>
<c.translation>(Munechika, heir to a house of proud tradition,)</c>

135
00:28:43.000 --> 00:29:06.000
<c.transcription>心安く思ひて下向し給へ。</c>
<c.translation>(set your heart at rest and go home now.)</c>

136
00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:16.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］漢家本朝に於て剣の威徳。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] What you have told me of the power of the swords in China and Japan)</c>

137
00:29:16.000 --> 00:29:25.000
<c.transcription>時に取つての祝言申す。はかりのく候。</c>
<c.translation>(has gladdened my heart at this important hour.)</c>

138
00:29:25.000 --> 00:29:31.000
<c.transcription>さて／＼御身は如何なる人ぞ。</c>
<c.translation>(Yet, I press you again to tell me who you are.)</c>

139
00:29:31.000 --> 00:29:40.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］よし誰なりとも頼むべし。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] Who I may be is of no consequence, but you must pray!)</c>

140
00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:47.000
<c.transcription>まづ／＼勅の御剣を。</c>
<c.translation>(Before anything else adorn your forge mound)</c>

141
00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:54.000
<c.transcription>打つべき壇を飾りつつ。</c>
<c.translation>(where you will temper the Imperial blade.)</c>

142
00:29:54.000 --> 00:30:06.000
<c.transcription>その時我を待ち給はゞ。</c>
<c.translation>(And at that time, if you will but wait for me.)</c>

143
00:30:07.000 --> 00:30:16.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］通力の身を変じ。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] I will change into supernatural form.)</c>

144
00:30:16.000 --> 00:30:25.000
<c.transcription>通力の身を変じて。</c>
<c.translation>(Having changed into a supernatural form,)</c>

145
00:30:25.000 --> 00:30:32.000
<c.transcription>必ずその時節に</c>
<c.translation>(I will come without fail, at the appointed time,)</c>

146
00:30:32.000 --> 00:30:43.000
<c.transcription>参り会ひて御力を。つけ申すべし。</c>
<c.translation>(and join you, adding my strength to yours.)</c>

147
00:30:43.000 --> 00:30:48.000
<c.transcription>待ち給へと。</c>
<c.translation>(Then wait for me!)</c>

148
00:30:48.000 --> 00:30:52.000
<c.transcription>夕雲の稲荷山。</c>
<c.translation>(So saying, into the evening clouds of Mt. Inari)</c>

149
00:30:52.000 --> 00:30:59.000
<c.transcription>行くへも知らず失せにけり</c>
<c.translation>(without a sign of where he went, he vanished,)</c>

150
00:30:59.000 --> 00:31:20.000
<c.transcription>行くへも知らず失せにけり。</c>
<c.translation>(Without a sign of where he went, he vanished.)</c>

151
00:34:49.000 --> 00:35:01.000
<c.transcription>斯様に候者は、稲荷大明神に</c>
<c.translation>([KYŌGEN] I am the god of a subsidiary shrine)</c>

152
00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:09.000
<c.transcription>仕へ申す末社の神にて候、</c>
<c.translation>(and in the service of Inari-daimyōjin.)</c>

153
00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:19.000
<c.transcription>只今是へ出ずること、余の義にあらず、</c>
<c.translation>(I have come here before you now on a matter of no small importance.)</c>

154
00:35:19.000 --> 00:35:30.000
<c.transcription>さても、人皇六十六代一條院、</c>
<c.translation>(Now then, it seems that the Emperor Ichijo, sixty-sixth of the imperial line,)</c>

155
00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:39.000
<c.transcription>この程、不思議の御告げましまして、</c>
<c.translation>(has recently had a portentous dream oracle.)</c>

156
00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:45.000
<c.transcription>三条の小鍛冶宗近に、</c>
<c.translation>(According to it, the Sanjo swordsmith Munechika,)</c>

157
00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:54.000
<c.transcription>御剣を打たせらるべきとの御事なり、</c>
<c.translation>(must be ordered to forge a blade.)</c>

158
00:35:54.000 --> 00:36:04.000
<c.transcription>すなわち道成卿、勅使となって、</c>
<c.translation>(At that time Minister Michinari was the imperial envoy)</c>

159
00:36:04.000 --> 00:36:11.000
<c.transcription>宣旨の趣き、仰られければ、</c>
<c.translation>(who gave him the details of the imperial message.)</c>

160
00:36:11.000 --> 00:36:17.000
<c.transcription>宗近、宣旨承り</c>
<c.translation>(Munechika hearing the message, agreed to comply with the order,)</c>

161
00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:27.000
<c.transcription>いか程大事に御剣を、打ち申すには、</c>
<c.translation>(though to forge such an important blade,)</c>

162
00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:35.000
<c.transcription>それがし一人にては計らいがたし、</c>
<c.translation>(he said, was something he could not do by himself)</c>

163
00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:45.000
<c.transcription>われに劣らぬ相槌無くては叶わじとて、</c>
<c.translation>("As it will be impossible without an assistant of skill equal to my own,)</c>

164
00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:58.000
<c.transcription>先ずはご辞退なされ候が綸言汗の如し、</c>
<c.translation>(I should certainly refuse this order, but as this is a request from the Emperor himself,)</c>

165
00:36:58.000 --> 00:37:10.000
<c.transcription>且つは家の面目と存じ、お受けを申され候、</c>
<c.translation>(I know it would bring great shame to my house to decline and so I will accept it," he said.)</c>

166
00:37:10.000 --> 00:37:21.000
<c.transcription>さりながら、この度の御剣を打ち申すには</c>
<c.translation>(And so, as it would not be possible for him to forge the sword by himslef on this occasion,)</c>

167
00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:30.000
<c.transcription>それがし一人にては計らいがたし、</c>
<c.translation>(in order to do it he decided he must call on divine power,)</c>

168
00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:37.000
<c.transcription>神力を頼もうずるとて、</c>
<c.translation>(in other words, on Inari Daimyojin, his family's tutelary god.)</c>

169
00:37:37.000 --> 00:37:47.000
<c.transcription>すなわち、稲荷大明神は氏神なり</c>
<c.translation>(If indeed a deity could watch over his forge,)</c>

170
00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:57.000
<c.transcription>ことさら、鍛治を守り給う御神なれば、</c>
<c.translation>(he decided he must go at once and pray concerning the matter.)</c>

171
00:37:57.000 --> 00:38:05.000
<c.transcription>只今参詣仕り候う所に</c>
<c.translation>(As he did this so humbly, the god of the Inari shrine knew of it and,)</c>

172
00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:16.000
<c.transcription>忝くも当社明神ご存じあって</c>
<c.translation>(taking the form of a youth, appeared and met)</c>

173
00:38:16.000 --> 00:38:28.000
<c.transcription>仮に童子の姿と現じ宗近に行き合い、</c>
<c.translation>(with Munechika, and spoke to him.)</c>

174
00:38:28.000 --> 00:38:35.000
<c.transcription>御言葉を交わされ候、</c>
<c.translation>(Commonly, in our land there have been,)</c>

175
00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:41.000
<c.transcription>総じて、我が朝において、</c>
<c.translation>(from the Age of the Gods, two sacred swords.)</c>

176
00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:50.000
<c.transcription>神代より伝うる霊剣、二つあり、</c>
<c.translation>(The one called "Totsuka no Tsurugi", the Ten-span Sword)</c>

177
00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:59.000
<c.transcription>十束の剣と申すは、須佐之男命、</c>
<c.translation>(was used by Susanō-no-mikoto, when learning of the great serpent)</c>

178
00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:10.000
<c.transcription>出雲の国、斐の川上に、大蛇のありしを、</c>
<c.translation>(at the headwaters of the Hi River in the country of Izumo,)</c>

179
00:39:10.000 --> 00:39:20.000
<c.transcription>従え給いしも、この剣の威徳なり、</c>
<c.translation>(he destroyed it, due to the virtue of this sword.)</c>

180
00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:27.000
<c.transcription>又、叢雲の剣と申すは、</c>
<c.translation>(Then again, the sword called "Murakumo no Tsurugi" the Gathering Clouds Sword,)</c>

181
00:39:27.000 --> 00:39:38.000
<c.transcription>そのとき大蛇の尾にありし剣なり、</c>
<c.translation>(was the sword he found at that time in the tail of the great serpent.)</c>

182
00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:50.000
<c.transcription>又、人皇十二代景行天皇、第二の皇子</c>
<c.translation>(Then again, Yamatodake-no-mikoto the second son of Emperor Keikō,)</c>

183
00:39:50.000 --> 00:40:00.000
<c.transcription>日本武尊命東夷を平らげ給いしも、</c>
<c.translation>(the twelfth of the imperial line, subdued the people of the eastern lands,)</c>

184
00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:06.000
<c.transcription>その剣の威徳なり、</c>
<c.translation>(this also due to the virtue of that sword.)</c>

185
00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:18.000
<c.transcription>それよりあらため、草薙の剣とは、これを申すなり、</c>
<c.translation>(From that time, it was renamed and known as 'Kusanagi-no-Tsurugi" the Grass Cutting Sword.)</c>

186
00:40:18.000 --> 00:40:27.000
<c.transcription>そのほか、漢の高祖、三尺の剣、</c>
<c.translation>(In addition to these, there are the Han Emperor's Three Foot Sword,)</c>

187
00:40:27.000 --> 00:40:40.000
<c.transcription>干将莫耶の剣、唐土我が朝において</c>
<c.translation>(the Gan JIang and Mo Ye swords. He told him many stories)</c>

188
00:40:40.000 --> 00:40:50.000
<c.transcription>剣の威徳、ことごとく御物語なされ、</c>
<c.translation>(of the virtue of swords, both in China and in our own country.)</c>

189
00:40:50.000 --> 00:41:01.000
<c.transcription>汝も、名を得たる鍛治なれば、いずれにおとらざる</c>
<c.translation>("You, too, if you are a swordsmith of repute, will be able to forge a blade of equal merit.)</c>

190
00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:12.000
<c.transcription>御剣を打ち申すなり、鉄を鍛うて待つべし、</c>
<c.translation>(Prepare, temper the metal, and wait.")</c>

191
00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:19.000
<c.transcription>その時明神来現あって、</c>
<c.translation>(At that time, Myojin will appear and be your assistant)</c>

192
00:41:19.000 --> 00:41:28.000
<c.transcription>相槌を打たせらるべきとの御事なれば、</c>
<c.translation>(in forging the blade. This being the case,)</c>

193
00:41:28.000 --> 00:41:37.000
<c.transcription>宗近も、喜びの眉をひらき、</c>
<c.translation>(Munechika, his eyebrows relaxed in joy,)</c>

194
00:41:37.000 --> 00:41:44.000
<c.transcription>只今、下向仕りて候、</c>
<c.translation>(is even now coming this way to do these things.)</c>

195
00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:53.000
<c.transcription>総じて何事も、祈請をかけ申せば、</c>
<c.translation>(In this way then, whe prayers are offered)</c>

196
00:41:53.000 --> 00:42:00.000
<c.transcription>諸願成就疑いなし、</c>
<c.translation>(they shall be fulfilled, without a doubt.)</c>

197
00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:09.000
<c.transcription>かまえてその分、心得候え、</c>
<c.translation>(On this matter, rest assured,)</c>

198
00:42:09.000 --> 00:42:17.000
<c.transcription>心得候え、</c>
<c.translation>(rest assured.)</c>

199
00:46:00.000 --> 00:46:08.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］宗近勅に随つて</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Now, I, Munichika, in compliance with the Imperial Will)</c>

200
00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:14.000
<c.transcription>即ち壇にあがり</c>
<c.translation>(have accordingly ascended the dais to ward off impurities.)</c>

201
00:46:14.000 --> 00:46:22.000
<c.transcription>不浄を隔つる七重の注連</c>
<c.translation>(It is adorned with the Seven-fold Sacred Rope,)</c>

202
00:46:22.000 --> 00:46:30.000
<c.transcription>四方に本尊をかけ奉り</c>
<c.translation>(and in the four corners sacred images placed in reverence.)</c>

203
00:46:30.000 --> 00:46:47.000
<c.transcription>幣帛を捧げ　仰ぎ願はくは</c>
<c.translation>(I raise up this Sacred wand and make my petition.)</c>

204
00:46:47.000 --> 00:46:55.000
<c.transcription>人皇六十代</c>
<c.translation>(Now, in the reign of the Sixty-sixth Emperor Ichijo,)</c>

205
00:46:55.000 --> 00:47:00.000
<c.transcription>一条の院の御宇に</c>
<c.translation>(I have been honored greatly in my craft,)</c>

206
00:47:00.000 --> 00:47:08.000
<c.transcription>其職の誉を蒙る事</c>
<c.translation>(through no effort of my own,)</c>

207
00:47:08.000 --> 00:47:19.000
<c.transcription>これ私の力にあらず。</c>
<c.translation>(rather, I have held in trust those skills.)</c>

208
00:47:19.000 --> 00:47:28.000
<c.transcription>伊弉諾伊弉冉の尊</c>
<c.translation>(When Izanagi and Izanami crossed over)</c>

209
00:47:28.000 --> 00:47:35.000
<c.transcription>天の浮橋を踏みわたり</c>
<c.translation>(the Floating Bridge of Heaven,)</c>

210
00:47:35.000 --> 00:47:45.000
<c.transcription>豊芦原を探り給ひし</c>
<c.translation>(and probed the Abundant Reed Plain)</c>

211
00:47:45.000 --> 00:47:52.000
<c.transcription>御矛より始まれり。</c>
<c.translation>(with the Sacred Spear was their beginning.)</c>

212
00:47:52.000 --> 00:48:01.000
<c.transcription>その後南瞻僧伽陀国波斯</c>
<c.translation>(Later, from holy Hashimida of Eastern India)</c>

213
00:48:01.000 --> 00:48:08.000
<c.transcription>弥陀尊者より此方</c>
<c.translation>(the descendants of Amakuni and Fujito)</c>

214
00:48:08.000 --> 00:48:21.000
<c.transcription>天国ひつきの子孫に伝へて</c>
<c.translation>(learned arts)</c>

215
00:48:21.000 --> 00:48:29.000
<c.transcription>今に至れり。</c>
<c.translation>(which I am now the master of.)</c>

216
00:48:31.000 --> 00:48:43.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］願はくは</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] Now, I pray!)</c>

217
00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:53.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］願はくは</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Now I petition: It is not for the glory of my name: Munechika,)</c>

218
00:48:53.000 --> 00:49:11.000
<c.transcription>宗近私の功名にあらず。</c>
<c.translation>(but at the imperial command of the Emperor,)</c>

219
00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:27.000
<c.transcription>普天卒土の勅命によれり</c>
<c.translation>(whose rule extends from heaven to earth, that I call on all divine beings,)</c>

220
00:49:27.000 --> 00:49:42.000
<c.transcription>さあらば十方恒沙の諸神</c>
<c.translation>(numberless as the sand of the Ganges,)</c>

221
00:49:42.000 --> 00:50:04.000
<c.transcription>唯今の宗近に力を合はせてたび給へとて。</c>
<c.translation>(to join your strength now with Munechika.)</c>

222
00:50:04.000 --> 00:50:12.000
<c.transcription>幣帛を捧げつゝ</c>
<c.translation>(I offer up this sacred wand.)</c>

223
00:50:12.000 --> 00:50:34.000
<c.transcription>天に仰ぎ頭を地に付け。骨髄の丹誠聞き入れ</c>
<c.translation>(I bow my head before heaven as I seek divine aid from my inmost being.)</c>

224
00:50:34.000 --> 00:50:51.000
<c.transcription>納受。せしめ給へや。</c>
<c.translation>(Hear and grant my prayer.)</c>

225
00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:59.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］謹上</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] With profound reverence:)</c>

226
00:50:59.000 --> 00:51:12.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］再拝</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] My supplication!)</c>

227
00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:46.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］いかにや宗近勅の剣。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Now, Munechika -- the Imperial Blade!)</c>

228
00:52:52.000 --> 00:53:02.000
<c.transcription>いかにや宗近勅の剣</c>
<c.translation>(Now, Munechika -- the Imperial Blade!)</c>

229
00:53:02.000 --> 00:53:10.000
<c.transcription>打つべき時節は虚空に知れり。</c>
<c.translation>(The appointed time for forging is known!)</c>

230
00:53:10.000 --> 00:53:23.000
<c.transcription>頼めや頼め唯たのめ。</c>
<c.translation>(Trust and have faith!  Only trust!)</c>

231
00:54:14.000 --> 00:54:33.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］童男壇の。上にあがり。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] A young boy ascends the forge mound!)</c>

232
00:54:33.000 --> 00:54:46.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］童男壇の。上にあがつて</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] A young boy ascends the forge mound,)</c>

233
00:54:46.000 --> 00:54:55.000
<c.transcription>宗近に三拝の膝を屈し。</c>
<c.translation>(kneels and bows three times before Munechika.)</c>

234
00:54:55.000 --> 00:55:04.000
<c.transcription>扨御剣の。鉄はと問へば</c>
<c.translation>("Now then, the metal for the blade?" he says)</c>

235
00:55:04.000 --> 00:55:13.000
<c.transcription>宗近も恐悦の心をさきとして</c>
<c.translation>(and Munechika, his heart joyful, in reply)</c>

236
00:55:13.000 --> 00:55:17.000
<c.transcription>鉄取り出し。</c>
<c.translation>(brings for the metal.)</c>

237
00:55:17.000 --> 00:55:28.000
<c.transcription>教の鎚をはつたと打てば。</c>
<c.translation>(As he strikes the first blow with his mallet,)</c>

238
00:55:28.000 --> 00:55:38.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］丁と打つ。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] Clang! we strike!)</c>

239
00:55:38.000 --> 00:55:41.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］丁</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Clang!)</c>

240
00:55:41.000 --> 00:55:45.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］丁と</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] Clang, again.)</c>

241
00:55:45.000 --> 00:55:55.000
<c.transcription>［地謡］打ち重ねたる鎚の響。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] The blows coming, one on another, the sound of their mallets)</c>

242
00:55:55.000 --> 00:56:10.000
<c.transcription>天地に聞こえて おびたゝしや</c>
<c.translation>(echoes throughout heaven and earth - How it resounds!)</c>

243
00:56:11.000 --> 00:56:17.000
<c.transcription>［ワキ］かくて御剣を打ち奉り。</c>
<c.translation>([WAKI] And so the Imperial Blade is forged:)</c>

244
00:56:17.000 --> 00:56:22.000
<c.transcription>表に小鍛冶宗近と打つ。</c>
<c.translation>(On the face of it I strike: "Munechika, Swordsmith"!)</c>

245
00:56:22.000 --> 00:56:29.000
<c.transcription>［シテ］神体時の弟子なれば。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] As your timely apprentice the god:)</c>

246
00:56:29.000 --> 00:56:39.000
<c.transcription>小狐と裏にあざやかに。</c>
<c.translation>("Little Fox", I skillfully strike on the reverse.)</c>

247
00:56:40.000 --> 00:56:50.000
<c.transcription>打ち奉る御剣の。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] Along the edge of the blade are beaten traces)</c>

248
00:56:50.000 --> 00:57:00.000
<c.transcription>刃は雲を乱したれば。</c>
<c.translation>(like wild clustering clouds.)</c>

249
00:57:00.000 --> 00:57:12.000
<c.transcription>天の叢雲ともこれなれや。</c>
<c.translation>("Clustering Clouds of Heaven", it will be!)</c>

250
00:57:12.000 --> 00:57:23.000
<c.transcription>天下第一の。</c>
<c.translation>([SHITE] First under Heaven:)</c>

251
00:57:23.000 --> 00:57:29.000
<c.transcription>天下第一の。</c>
<c.translation>([JIUTAI] First under Heaven:)</c>

252
00:57:29.000 --> 00:57:36.000
<c.transcription>二つの銘の御剣にて。</c>
<c.translation>(The sword with two inscriptions!)</c>

253
00:57:36.000 --> 00:57:43.000
<c.transcription>四海を治め給へば。</c>
<c.translation>(It will rule the land to the four seas,)</c>

254
00:57:43.000 --> 00:57:49.000
<c.transcription>五穀成就も此時なれや。</c>
<c.translation>(celebrate the abundance of the five staple crops.)</c>

255
00:57:49.000 --> 00:57:55.000
<c.transcription>即ち汝が氏の神。</c>
<c.translation>("I, before you, as the deity of your clan:)</c>

256
00:57:55.000 --> 00:58:02.000
<c.transcription>稲荷の神体小狐丸を。</c>
<c.translation>(the manifestation of Inari: the Little Fox,)</c>

257
00:58:02.000 --> 00:58:08.000
<c.transcription>勅使に捧げ申し。</c>
<c.translation>(come to aid you in fulfilling your task.)</c>

258
00:58:08.000 --> 00:58:13.000
<c.transcription>これまでなりと言ひ捨てゝ。</c>
<c.translation>(Now, I am done!" So saying, takes his leave.)</c>

259
00:58:13.000 --> 00:58:18.000
<c.transcription>又群雲に飛び乗り。</c>
<c.translation>(Once more he leaps upon the mass of clouds,)</c>

260
00:58:18.000 --> 00:58:25.000
<c.transcription>又群雲に飛びのりて</c>
<c.translation>(Again, more he leaps upon the mass of clouds,)</c>

261
00:58:25.000 --> 00:58:52.000
<c.transcription>東山稲荷の峯にぞ帰りける。</c>
<c.translation>(and return to Higashiyama, the eastern mountains, the peak of Mt. Inari!)</c>